    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-24T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.01/107</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-24T23:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1916, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Resignation of President Yuan is believed to be impending. It has been intimated
                    to me from him that should he resign he is likely to request the hospitality and
                    protection of the American Legation as he prefers to go to United States rather
                    than to Japan whose protection has been offered him. If thus appealed to, in my
                    opinion, no alternative but to afford asylum and to protect transit to a
                    seaport.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
